# Selcom Payments — Safety Rules

## Webhook handling

- Payment state changes ONLY from the Selcom webhook — never from a frontend
  "Nimeshalipa" button (that button may only re-query current status).
- Every webhook handler MUST be idempotent: check `paid_at` / transaction status
  before activating, disbursing commission, or creating ledger rows. Duplicate
  callbacks from Selcom are normal and must be no-ops the second time.
- Verify: matching order_id, matching amount (paid >= required), and signature
  when available. Log and reject mismatches; never partially activate.

## Commission rules

- Commission disbursement is money leaving the company. It must be guarded by
  `commission_issued_at IS NULL` checks and recorded before external calls.
- In the new BEAT flow: commission moves to INSTALLED status, not PAID.

## Subscription dates

- `starts_at`/`ends_at` represent the SERVICE period. In the new flow they are set
  at installation time (INSTALLED), not payment time. Do not reset dates on
  repeated webhook deliveries.

## Environment

- Selcom credentials live in `.env.production` on the VPS (Laravel reads that file
  in production, not `.env`). Required keys: SELCOM_API_KEY, SELCOM_API_SECRET,
  SELCOM_VENDOR, SELCOM_PIN, SELCOM_BASE_URL, SELCOM_WEBHOOK_URL,
  SELCOM_REDIRECT_URL, SELCOM_CANCEL_URL.
- Selcom whitelists the server IP. New server = request whitelist BEFORE go-live
  (error signature: `Authentication failed. Source IP not whitelisted (4032)`).
- Never hard-code credentials; never log secrets or full signatures.
